The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Poland captain injured
                                                                                                                                                                                                     DIARY
                      
	Poland captain injured   
	Bad Waltersdorf (Austria): Poland captain Maciej Zurawski was ruled out of the group stage of Euro 2008 on Monday after straining his right quadriceps.  
	Team doctor Jerzy Grzywocz said the striker underwent an MRI scan in Vienna after injuring his leg in Polands opening 0-2 loss to Germany on Sunday. Mariusz Lewandowski also sat out Polands light training session Monday afternoon with a bruised left ankle.         
	Frei urges team to fight on         
	 Feusisberg (Switzerland): Injured striker Alexander Frei urged Switzerland on Monday to fight without him for the European Championship after admitting that his own dream is destroyed. In an emotional news conference, the teams captain and record scorer explained his bitter disappointment at being ruled out after rupturing his left knee ligament in Switzerlands 0-1 loss to the Czech Republic on Saturday.         
	Noble cause         
	 Vienna: Uefa is promoting a charity initiative of the Red Cross that encourages fans to support their team at the European Championship and help land mine victims in Afghanistan. In a program labeled Score for the Red Cross, people can buy virtual goals online that will cost $1.58 each and a ranking system will show which Euro 2008 team has the most generous fans.                                                                                                                            
